Zurich-West – From Industrial Quarter to Trendy District
The district in the west of Zurich is full of contrasts, boasting an unpolished charm. But wait, there's more! Within a mere 10-minute walk, you'll find yourself standing in front of not one, not two, but two rivers and a magnificent lake. It's like nature put on a show just for you.

And if you're feeling adventurous, the central train station is only a 5-minute walk away. If you're crazy enough to want to see another town, it's only a hop, skip, and a jump away. It's Switzerland after all, where nothing is too far away.

I live alone in this great property and would like to give up on tourists and nice and clean guests the chance to stay with me so that they can get to know Zurich.
I work irregularly, but always sleep at home.
Have two cats (Leonardo and Sissi 6 years old) but have nothing against new roommates have. You are very nice!
Free internet

Auf Deutsch
Ich wohne seit 3 Jahren in Zürich - Seebach und habe mir eine tolle Wohnung gekauft.  Das Gästezimmer liegt ca 20 Minuten von der City entfernt, kann aber mit der Strassenbahn Nr. 14 gut erreicht werden. 

Ich wohne solo in dieser tollen Eigentums Wohnung und möchte gerne aufgestellten  Touristen und netten und sauberen Gästen die Chance geben bei mir zu übernachten, damit sie Zürich kennen lernen.

Habe zwei Katzen (Leonardo und Sissi 6 Jahre alt) welche aber nichts gegen neue Mitbewohner haben. Sie sind sehr lieb! Auch ab 22.09.2017 habe ich einen Tierschutz Hund. welcher aus Spanien kommt und 2 Jahre alt ist.

name: Home in Zurich · ★4.86 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
host_about:
In between travels I have been working in London, Barcelona, and Melbourne. In Australia I have also been a volunteer for the rainforest protection movement and for WWOOF. Before I retired I have been working for the gardens and lands department of Zurich helping the employees with their IT issues. When I travel I am missing Bürli bread and chocolate yoghourt. I am married to Elisangela who is from rural Brasil. She works preparing lunch for a lot of school children and she is also verger of an old pretty church in Zurich. Elisangela misses her home land and calls her parents every day. 

I have read about Airbnb businesses who are already more like a hotels because they are listing so many accommodations, and I counted I am also listing 10 accommodations. One of then is an old couple who have a cute cottage in their garden. We always like to meet them. What I get from Airbnb I entirely pass to them and they give me from the delicious eggs of their chicken sometimes. Two rooms that I am listing are from a friend whose house was too empty after his wife died. Now the house is much livelier and he also seems much happier again. He thinks I should get something for making those contacts, even if I never expected it. Three listings are actually only one holiday house that we own, but during the Film Festival in Locarno I only rent two rooms and I make breakfast because then we always have very good conversations under the kaki tree. Our own accommodations are not so perfect and therefore I try to describe them very well, hoping that sophisticated people won't even consider staying with us. 

Airbnb says it is not a hotel, but I always get messages trying to encourage me for instant booking. I think that instant booking should be something exclusively for hotels. If people do not have a meaningful profile or if they won't tell anything about themselves then I might not even answer their requests.

neighborhood_overview:
From Zurich HB, get off 2 Metro stops at S4 Giesshubel, and S10 Binz station almost comes to the door my apartment from Zurich main station, so it's very convenient. S4 runs every 20 minutes. In addition there are one tram station for tram 5 and 13, and a bus stop (Manesseplatz) for bus 72 (to Escher-Wyss-Platz) station nearby. Take the S4 subway, unless you have a GPS or a map! It takes about 30 minutes to get here from the Zurich Airport according to (website hidden) maps, if you are right on train schedule. I would say 60 minutes is more realistic.

In Manesseplatz is next to Schmiede Wiedikon where locals hang out. Famous Tattoo shop, Ink Tank across the street. There is also a restaurant with a yellow sign of a fork and knife across the apartment. There are nice restaurants around to discover. However, Zurich prices are very high.

Super convenient to just hop on the S10 train nearby at Binz to go straight to the top of the mountain at Uetliberg in 15 minu

"Peace cannot be kept by force. It can only be achieved by understanding. You cannot subjugate a nation forcibly unless you wipe out every man, woman, and child. Unless you wish to use such drastic measures, you must find a way of settling your disputes without resort to arms." 
- Albert Einstein

"All of science is nothing more than the refinement of everyday thinking."
- Albert Einstein

"Now he has departed from this strange world a little ahead of me. That means nothing. People like us, who believe in physics, know that the distinction between past, present, and future is only a stubbornly persistent illusion."
- Albert Einstein

"We cannot expect to cross the rainbow bridge through a good act of contrition; that will not be sufficient. We have to understand." - Terrence McKenna

"Hastiness and superficiality are the psychic diseases of the twentieth century, and more than anywhere else this illness is reflected in the press." - Alexandr Solzhenitsyn

"My ultimate dream is to sow seeds in the desert. To revegetate the deserts is to sow seed in people's hearts." - Masanobu Fukuoka

"Men tend to have the beliefs that suit their passions. Cruel men believe in a cruel God, and use their belief to excuse their cruelty. Only kindly men believe in a kindly God, and they would be kindly in any case." - Bertrand Russell

"Live as if you were living for the second time and had acted as wrongly the first time as you are about to act now." - Viktor Frankl

"The sick individual finds himself at home with all other similarly sick individuals. The whole culture is geared to this kind of pathology. The result is that the average individual does not experience the separateness and isolation the fully schizophrenic person feels. He feels at ease among those who suffer from the same deformation; in fact, it is the fully sane person who feels isolated in the insane society — and he may suffer so much from the incapacity to communicate that it is he who may become psychotic. In the context of this study the crucial question is whether the hypothesis of a quasi-autistic or of low-grade schizophrenic disturbance would help us to explain some of the violence spreading today." - Erich Fromm

"World War III is a guerrilla information war with no division between military and civilian participation." - Marshall Mcluhan

"Reason is a harmonising, controlling force rather than a creative one. Even in the most purely logical realms, it is insight that first arrives at what is new." 
- Bertrand Russell

Don't cry because it's over, smile because it happened. 
- Dr. Seuss

“It’s more important to know what sort of person has a disease than to know what sort of disease a person has.” 
― Hippocrates

neighborhood_overview:
From Zurich HB (mainstation), get off 2 Metro stops at S4 Giesshubel, and S10 Binz station almost comes to the door my apartment from Zurich main station, so it's very convenient. In addition there are one tram station for tram 5 and 13, and a bus stop (Manesseplatz) for bus 72 (to Escher-Wyss-Platz) station nearby. Take the S4 unless you have GPS or a map! It takes about 30 minutes to get here from the Zurich Airport according to (website hidden) maps, if you are right on train schedule. I would say 60 minutes is more realistic.

In Manesseplatz is next to Schmiede Wiedikon where locals hang out. Famous Tattoo shop, Ink Tank across the street. There is also a restaurant with a yellow sign of a fork and knife across the apartment. There are nice restaurants around to discover. However, Zurich prices are very high.

Super convenient to just hop on the S10 train nearby at Binz to go straight to the top of the mountain at Uetliberg in 15 minutes, walk 5 minutes

name: Rental unit in Zurich · ★4.93 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1.5 shared baths
neighborhood_overview:
Wollishofen-Kilchberg is a very green, quiet and first of all residential area. Due to its characteristics and proximity to the center it is in high demand. It offers nice views into green gardens, panoramic views over the lake and the mountains.
You will be woken up by birdsongs and not by traffic.
Some of the nicest lakeside bars and restaurants you can find along the Lake Zürich are nearby. (lf you look at the map indication of my listing click on the icons for restaurants or point of views you will find around my place to get some ideas.)
Also the famous LINDT chocolate factory and there gorgeous outlet shop is located nearby and you can often smell a slight fragrance of chocolate in the air.
To have space, peace, a safe neighborhood and a lot of green around is what I love most living here and would like to share with you.
host_about:
“It is passion that makes man live;  reason makes one only last.” 
― Nicolas Chamfort
"Durch die Leidenschaften lebt der Mensch, durch die Vernunft existiert er bloss."

This is my motto  in life and I try to live up to it as much as I can. I have traveled extensively for work and leisure and made invaluable experiences during my trips. I am passionate about wine, food, exotic herbs and plants. But nothing beats good company and great talks! My home is my castle I love and I care about. You are welcome to share and enjoy it with me.

I am an easy going, open minded person with a lot of interests.  I love reading  and I am an "old school" newspaper addict. On a Sunday morning you will most likely find me on the sofa surrounded by newspapers and magazines and well equipped with coffee and cookies to indulge in what is going on in the world. 
*******************************************************************
Note to Guests
• I enjoy meeting people and like to know who my guests are. Write a bit about yourself and your purpose of travelling. That way I not only get a better picture of you but can come up with valuable information and ideas to make your arrival and stay pleasent, convenient and memorable.
• A novel of your life story isn't necessary; just write about what you think someone meeting you for the first time would want to know.

name: Home in Zürich · ★4.42 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview: Das legendären "Dörfli" ist Ausflugsziel für viele Touristen aus der Agglomeration, der übrigen Schweiz und natürlich auch von Gästen aus dem Ausland. Weil dem seit Generationen so ist, ist das Angebot organisch gewachsen ... es gibt es fast kein Wunsch dem die hiesige Gastronomie nicht entsprechen kann ...
host_about:
Als vielbeschäftigte Mutter, bin ich auch Wirtin der Aelpli-Bar. Dort gibt es auf der Welt einzigartig jeden Tag frische Aelpli-Milch ab 17.00 Uhr und ab 20.00 Uhr, dazu live Musik. Die Aelpli-Bar ist seit Generationen ein Treffpunkt von Schweizer Volksmusikern, die hier gerne auch ihre STUBETE abhalten. Weil diese Künstler aus der ganzen Schweiz hier auftreten gibt es ab und zu Bedarf sie für die Nacht unterzubringen. Oft blieben diese Kammern aber leer, so habe ich die Gelegenheit am Schopf gepackt und biete sie auf airbnb an. 
Sollte Du den Wunsch hegen persönlich in Kontakt mit Einheimischen zu kommen fühle Dich bitte in der Aelpli-Bar wie zu Hause.

name: Townhouse in Zurich · ★4.95 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · Shared half-bath
neighborhood_overview:
After a long sightseeing tour, you have the opportunity to immerse yourself in another world and relax on a walk in the nearby forest. There stands as a "sight with history" a large water-spitting elephant in Wehrenbach

Or the Loorenturm, a 30 meter high wooden structure, from which you can enjoy a view in clear weather up to the Bernese, Central Swiss and Glarus Alps

Also, a jogging round, overlooking the lake, offers along the ridge. The way leads through the old core of the aera and you suddenly feel like in the countryside

A short drive away is the Bad Fohrbach, with swimming pool, indoor pool and a heated outdoor spa pool. Also, various massages are offered

The Fifa headquarters, the zoo and the Masoala hall are also nearby

To end the day with culinary delights, there is an Indian restaurant nearby, a special steakhouse or a former cowshed for rustic food etc.

name: Rental unit in Zurich · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
host_about: I am scientist working in Swiss Federal Institute of Technology (ETH) in Zurich. I teach Image Analysis and work on various scientific projects related to genetics and cancer treatments. I am very relaxed person and I follow only few rules in life: I do not use comb, I do not hurry and I respect everyone disregarding age, status or foot size. I do believe in surf and laugh.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.82 · 2 bedrooms · 4 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This is a very lively area in the middle of restaurants, bars and  nightlife. The media call it the Hipster-Area of Zürich. Its a paradise for people who loves culture: There are 100 Restaurants, Bars, Cafes, etc. of all kinds in walking distance from the apartement. You can get Food from Swiss. India. Thai. name: Townhouse in Zürich · ★4.92 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1.5 shared baths
neighborhood_overview:
After a long sightseeing tour, you have the opportunity to immerse yourself in another world and relax on a walk in the nearby forest. There stands as a "sight with history" a large water-spitting elephant in Wehrenbach

Or the Loorenturm, a 30 m high wooden structure, from which you can enjoy a view in clear weather up to the Bernese, Central Swiss and Glarus Alps.

Also, a jogging round, overlooking the lake, along the ridge. The way leads through the old core of the area and you suddenly feel like in the countryside.

A short drive away is the Bad Fohrbach, with swimming pool, indoor pool and a heated outdoor spa pool. Also, various massages are offered.

The Fifa headquarters, the zoo and the Masoala hall are also nearby

To end the day with culinary delights, there is an Indian restaurant nearby, a special steakhouse or a former cowshed for rustic food etc.

With my Airbnb hosting I try to accommodate to my guests needs and wishes but also expect some flexibility from your side since I have a day job and am mostly not at home during the day. But so far we always managed to work something out.

If you make a reservation with me I will give you plenty of ideas about what to do in Zurich before you arrive and am also more than happy to tell you about some hidden spots and local specialties once we meet in person.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Zurich-West – From Industrial Quarter to Trendy District

The district in the west of Zurich is full of contrasts, boasting an unpolished charm.

Where ships were once built and engines bolted together, art, design, food, culture shopping and architecture are now the center of attention. Factories have moved away, leaving their vast expanses of space that creative minds have taken advantage of.

Beneath the railway arches, design boutiques and market halls have moved in at what's know as "Im Viadukt" – and on the Gerolds-Areal you find Frau Gerolds Garten (Mrs. Gerold's Garden), a city garden and catering establishment. Besides the Freitag Flagship Store, diverse second hand furniture stores are also on the spot. On the other side of the Hardbrücke (bridge) the 126m Prime Tower reigns – boasting number-one place as Switzerland's highest building until the opening of the Roche Towers in Basel.

We love Art and Design, music, cooking, gardening, the mountains and opening our door to friends and guests…

There are so many different supermarkets, places to eat and shop just 150m away! Although I highly recommend exploring the area with a "fresh" pair of eyes, here are the things I'd vouch for:

Bar "Nordbrücke" – Open almost all days, great selection of drinks, spinning sessions by local DJs on weekends (can get crowded by then).

"The Artisan" – awesome craft beer/dinner place with very good fresh produce and great "bière blonde" as well as more freaky nuances of beer.

"Ultimo Bacio"– organic supermarket with everything your organic heart craves for. Very extensive selection of fine chocolates (in case you want to bring some home) and great bread.

Apart from that, you'll find an ice cream shop, an Italian restaurant, supermarkets, a bakery, and just about everything you need around these places in no less than 200m distance from the flat.

The one thing I couldn't live without is

Sounds stupid but I just want to spend my time intensively. 



Have a nice day!

The hotel is conveniently located near the Zurich Oerlikon train station, which is just a 5-minute walk away. The hotel is also close to several restaurants, cafes, and shops, as well as the Hallenstadion arena, event halls 662 and 550 and the Messe Zurich exhibition center.

The surrounding area is a mix of residential and commercial buildings, with a lively atmosphere and plenty of activity.

Supermarkets are qickly reachable.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
Rental unit in Zürich · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1.5 shared baths
neighborhood_overview:
Wollishofen-Kilchberg is a very green, quiet and first of all residential area. Due to its characteristics and proximity to the center it is in high demand. It offers nice views into green gardens, panoramic views over the lake and the mountains.
You will be woken up by birdsongs and not by traffic.
Some of the nicest lakeside bars and restaurants you can find along the Lake Zürich are nearby. (lf you look at the map indication of my listing click on the icons for restaurants or point of views you will find around my place to get some ideas.)
Also the famous LINDT chocolate factory and there gorgeous outlet shop is located nearby and you can often smell a slight fragrance of chocolate in the air.
To have space, peace, a safe neighborhood and a lot of green around is what I love most living here and would like to share with you.
host_about:
“It is passion that makes man live;  reason makes one only last.” 
― Nicolas Chamfort
"Durch die Leidenschaften lebt der Mensch, durch die Vernunft existiert er bloss."

This is my motto  in life and I try to live up to it as much as I can. I have traveled extensively for work and leisure and made invaluable experiences during my trips. I am passionate about wine, food, exotic herbs and plants. But nothing beats good company and great talks! My home is my castle I love and I care about. You are welcome to share and enjoy it with me.

I am an easy going, open minded person with a lot of interests.  I love reading  and I am an "old school" newspaper addict. On a Sunday morning you will most likely find me on the sofa surrounded by newspapers and magazines and well equipped with coffee and cookies to indulge in what is going on in the world. 
*******************************************************************
Note to Guests
• I enjoy meeting people and like to know who my guests are. Write a bit about yourself and your purpose of travelling. That way I not only get a better picture of you but can come up with valuable information and ideas to make your arrival and stay pleasent, convenient and memorable.
• A novel of your life story isn't necessary; just write about what you think someone meeting you for the first time would want to know.

name: Bed and breakfast in Zürich · ★4.63 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is close to the Zurich West business district. Many larger companies and bank office buildings are in the immediate vicinity. Altstetten train station can be reached on foot in six minutes. Various tram and bus lines connect the apartment house with the city center of Zurich in 10 minutes. Zurich Airport can be reached by car in 20 minutes via the Zurich-Altstetten motorway junction. The Letzipark shopping center is 500 meters away, and the Letzigrund football stadium is right next to it. Bars and art galleries are within walking distance of our hotel in Zurich West and the local recreation area of ​​the Uetliberg is ideal for long walks.

Our guests enjoy 48 special conditions in the nearby david gym fitness center. Letzigrund, the home stadium of the FC Zürich and GC Zürich football clubs, hosts many interesting matches. The stadium is also used as the annual venue for the world-class athletics meeting in Zurich, as well as regularly for large open-air concert
host_about:
Lieber Gast,

herzlichen Dank für Ihr Interesse an unserem Unternehmen THE FLAG Zürich. Damit Sie sich auch in Zeiten von Corona sicher und wohl während Ihres Aufenthalts bei uns fühlen, möchten wir Ihnen im Folgenden einige Hinweise geben.
Wir möchten Sie darauf aufmerksam machen, dass aufgrund der aktuellen Coronapandemie in unserem Hotel eine strenge Maskenpflicht gilt. Bitte Tragen Sie eine Maske, sobald Sie Ihr Hotelzimmer verlassen und sich in öffentlichen Bereichen (Lobby, Flur, Aufzug, Tiefgarage etc.) aufhalten. Die Maske muss immer die Nase und den Mund bedecken.

Darüber hinaus möchten wir Sie darauf hinweisen, dass sich stets nur die bei der Buchung angegebene Anzahl an Personen in den Hotelzimmern aufhalten darf. Der Aufenthalt von weiteren Personen, Besuch oder Ähnlichem ist nicht gestattet. Wir behalten uns vor, unser Hausrecht bei Zuwiderhandlung (notfalls polizeilich) geltend zu machen. Feiern, Partys oder ähnliche Ansammlungen in den Hotelzimmern sind strengstens verboten. 

Sicherheitskaution:
Bei Check-In benötigen wir eine Garantie über die Summe Ihres Aufenthaltes sowie CHF 200.00 für mögliche Extras als Sicherheitskaution. Diese kann bei Anreise in Form von Bargeld, EC- oder Kreditkarte hinterlegt werden. Eine Rückerstattung erfolgt unmittelbar nach Ihrer Abreise. Das Hotel kann zudem eine Kopie Ihres Ausweises anfertigen.

Nichtraucherhotel:
Das Rauchen ist in all unseren Hotelzimmern sowie in den öffentlichen Bereichen von THE FLAG Zürich strengstens untersagt. THE FLAG ist ein reines Nichtraucherhotel. Bei Verstoß gegen das Rauchverbot behalten wir uns vor, die Reinigungskosten (bis zu CHF 500.00) in Rechnung zu stellen bzw. mit der Sicherheitskaution zu verrechnen. Das Rauchen ist nur auf Balkonen und Terrassen erlaubt.

Sachbeschädigung und Haftung:
Hotel- und Übernachtungsgäste haften für Schäden oder übermäßige Verschmutzung, welche sie am Eigentum von THE FLAG verursachen. Schadensersatzzahlungen werden mit der Sicherheitskaution verrechnet bzw. gesondert in Rechnung gestellt. 

Nachtruhe:
Zwischen 22.00 und 07.00 Uhr bitten wir Sie, die Nachtruhe zu respektieren und andere Gäste nicht zu stören. Personen, die gegen die Hausruhe verstoßen, kann ein weiterer Aufenthalt im THE FLAG Zürich verweigert werden. Ebenfalls kann ein Hausverbot ausgesprochen werden.


Zuwiderhandlungen gegen die vorgenannten Regeln werden mit bis zu CHF 500.00 geahndet.

Vielen Dank für die Beachtung der Regeln. Sollten Sie Fragen zu Ihrem Aufenthalt haben, stehen wir Ihnen jederzeit gerne zur Verfügung.

Wir würden uns freuen, Sie bald als Gast begrüßen zu dürfen und wünschen Ihnen bis dahin noch eine schöne Zeit!  

Herzlichst,
Ihr THE FLAG Zürich Team

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in Zurich's third district ("Kreis 3, Alt-Wiedikon).

Kreis 3 lies to the south west of the city centre and is bordered by the river Sihl and parts of the Albis mountain range. It comprises Sihlfeld, Alt-Wiedikon and Friesenberg and is overlooked by Bühlkirche and behind this, Zurich’s “very own mountain” Uetliberg. Wiedikon became part of the city of Zürich in 1893 and it is now home to around 47,000 people.

Today, the district is mostly residential. If you wander through the streets of Kreis 3 (which I highly recommend) you’ll find numerous green spaces filled with picnicking families and school children, as well as a large number of antique stores, with some vintage clothing shops thrown in as well.

Wiedikon is home to a number of authentic and very satisfying Asian restaurants. You can find Vietnamese, Thai, Chinese, Indian and Japanese food. Mexican and Spanish cuisine is also available, as well as perennial Swiss, Italian

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.90 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
In the immediate vicinity of the local recreation areas along the Sihl, perfectly connected to public and private transport, with its own S-Bahn station and only a few minutes by train from the city centre: in Greencity, the city, nature and quality of life merge into a completely new neighbourhood concept.

Greencity is the first area in Switzerland to be consistently aligned with the goals of the 2000-watt society. The new quarter not only sets standards in terms of energy efficiency and environmental awareness. Greencity is also fully committed to the principles of sustainability with regard to coexistence and mobility.

A vital, urban mix of residential buildings and offices, shops, restaurants and public facilities is crucial. Greencity lies like an island between the surrounding nature and urban areas - and at the same time is always in the middle of modern life.

neighborhood_overview:
Wollishofen-Kilchberg is a very green and quiet, upscale residental area and offers nice views onto the lake and the mountains.

Some of the nicest bars and restaurants you can find along the Lake Zuerich are nearby.

IBM Research Labs, Swiss Re Centre for Global Dialogue, The GDI Institute/Think Tank and also the famous LINDT chocolate factory are located here (and you can often smell a slight fragrance of chocolate in the air...)
To have space, peace, a safe neighborhood and a lot of green around is what I love most about living here.
host_about:
“It is passion that makes man live;  reason makes one only last.” 
― Nicolas Chamfort
"Durch die Leidenschaften lebt der Mensch, durch die Vernunft existiert er bloss."

This is my motto  in life and I try to live up to it as much as I can. I have traveled extensively for work and leisure and made invaluable experiences during my trips. I am passionate about wine, food, exotic herbs and plants. But nothing beats good company and great talks! My home is my castle I love and I care about. You are welcome to share and enjoy it with me.

I am an easy going, open minded person with a lot of interests.  I love reading  and I am an "old school" newspaper addict. On a Sunday morning you will most likely find me on the sofa surrounded by newspapers and magazines and well equipped with coffee and cookies to indulge in what is going on in the world. 
*******************************************************************
Note to Guests
• I enjoy meeting people and like to know who my guests are. Write a bit about yourself and your purpose of travelling. That way I not only get a better picture of you but can come up with valuable information and ideas to make your arrival and stay pleasent, convenient and memorable.
• A novel of your life story isn't necessary; just write about what you think someone meeting you for the first time would want to know.

Enchanting Lakeside Neighborhood in Zurich
Welcome to our captivating neighborhood, beautifully nestled on the shores of Zurich Lake. Here, tranquility meets convenience, making it a perfect locale for both short and long-term stays.

- Tram stop in front of the house
- 6 min with direct tram to Paradeplatz
- 10 min with direct tram to Zurich Main Station

Our neighborhood is renowned for its scenic beauty, offering stunning views of Zurich Lake at every turn. Picturesque paths and parks surround the area, providing wonderful opportunities for leisurely strolls, morning jogs, or peaceful picnics overlooking the tranquil lake.

The neighborhood boasts a rich tapestry of charming houses and apartments, interspersed with vibrant foliage and mature trees. The serenity here is second to none, making it an ideal retreat from the city's hustle and bustle.
Despite its peaceful setting, the neighborhood does not compromise on convenience. A sho

The river limmat is only 10 minutes walk away and perfect to go jogging. For more sports you can go up the hill for 20 minutes where you find a Vitaparcours (sports parcours) in the forest.

Wipkingen is a part of Zürich that changes more and more into a hip place. I recommend a typical Swiss brunch at "Kafi Schnaps" or "Restaurant Nordbrücke".

Just on the other side of the river you find the new emerging "Zürich West" with many bars, clubs, restaurants and the Prime Tower (tallest building of Zürich with restaurant/lounge on the top).

neighborhood_overview:
Zu den Nachbarn: Unsere Beziehung zu den Nachbarinnen und Nachbarn ist eng und wir nehmen Rücksicht aufeinander. Es leben Personen unterschiedlichen Alters im Haus, darunter auch eine Familie mit zwei Kindern. Deshalb ist die Wohnung vor allem für ein Paar ab ca. 30 Jahren oder für eine Familie mit max. zwei Kindern geeignet. Für Jugendliche und sehr junge nachtaktive Erwachsene ist unsere Wohnung nicht geeignet.
Städtebauliche Situation: Das Haus ist 1926 gebaut worden und befindet sich in einem Wohnquartier mit fast ausschliesslich älteren und schönen Häusern. Es gibt viele Grünflächen, Bäume und Spielwiesen rund ums Haus und im umliegenden Quartier. Dennoch kann man den Hauptbahnhof zu Fuss in einer knappen Viertelstunde erreichen (!). In der Nähe gibt es mehrere Tramlinien, die die ganze Stadt erschliessen.
host_about: Tobias und ich wohnen seit vielen Jahren in dieser schönen Wohnung und freuen uns jeden Tag und schätzen uns glücklich, hier zu sein. Ich arbeite als Pflegedienstleitung in einem Alterszentrum und Tobias, mein Ehemann, arbeitet als Theaterwissenschaftler und als Lektor und Korrektor.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.85 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: You have everything close by: grocery stores, pharmacy, post office just 1-2 tram/bus stops away, they also can be reached by foot (max. 10 min.). There is a public outdoor swimming pool just 5-10 walking minutes away, it's open throughout the summer months and the adult entry fee costs 8 Fr.  You can reach the night life scene within 10-15 minutes by tram. There are also several nice cafés and restaurants in both tram directions, also all in walking distance. You'll find a small shopping centre (restaurants, grocery store, atm) and a bakery just around the corner and down the street (at the Berninaplatz tram station). Down the street you'll find an asian restaurant. There are also several parks in the area, the biggest (and probably nicest) one being at "Irchel", where the university is also located. The airport is just 15 minutes away from Berninaplatz (tram 10) or 4 minutes away from the Oerlikon train station (several trains). If you need any specific info, feel free to ask me.

host_about:
We are are a family of four, two school-girls, my husband, me and four bunnies named Frida, Sugar, Cruella & Armstrong.

We love to travel ourselves and enjoy being adventures and learning about new things, cultures and habits while we are abroad. Biggest love is Paris and New York; Tel Aviv has been a regular and can't be missed at least once a year, the food is divine! Actually bohemian-chic and boutique hotels are the places you would find us most. We appreciate the special gems around the globe.

At our home we are happy to share any inside tips with our guests, but of course are respecting the privacy of your stay. For that reason we're also expecting the privat area of ours to be valued.

My husband and I own a film production company and work with our team from the villa. Our big passion is film, has been always and still fascinates us every day. 

Cooking and hosting is another big love of mine, but the biggest is my family, for me I enjoy having quality time with them. Lucky us, the family even expands to a great group of dear friends, so our life is blessed with lot's of good energy and fine people.

Since we acquired the villa a few years ago, another joy finds its way into our environment; I absolutely love to decorate and interior design spaces. In little steps we've been renovating the house, giving it back it's old beauty. Amazing how it's changing step by step. Sharing it with guests is great. 

I am so curious about life and who we are in ourselves, I love the journey day by day!

name: Condo in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath

- 3 minutes walk to the number 3 tram stop, which stops at; Zurich Main Station and a number of other great eating and drinking destinations in the city (Langstrasee, Wiedikon, Lochergut, Hardbrucke, Letzigrund)
- Number 80 bus which will connect you to Trimelispital, Altstetten Station and Oerlikon
- Number 67 bus which will connect you to Wiedikon (popular night life area)
- Located next to 3 major supermarkets
- Very close to nature and Albisrieden forest and Uetliberg walking trails
- Letzigrund is a short ride on public transport or 15 minute walk
- Close to a number of large businesses (UBS, Siemens, Electrolux, IBM)
- if you are visiting by car and need to arrange parking there are a number of blue zone spots on Altstetterstrasse, close by.

Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.53 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Nestled in a prosperous neighbourhood, this apartment is surrounded by a rich tapestry of local cultures and traditions. Immerse yourself in the charm of the small ancient "village center," where you'll find all your daily necessities within easy reach. A leisurely stroll of approximately 1 kilometer will lead you to the vibrant Niederdorf, Zurich's old town, brimming with history and charm.

Explore the artistic side of Zurich with renowned museums such as the museum of art and Kulturama, both within walking distance. The vibrant theater scene and the picturesque Lake Zurich are also just a pleasant walk away, offering an array of recreational activities.

For an enchanting coffee experience, don't miss the hidden gem, Kafi Paradiesli, located at Hofstrasse 19, 8032 Zurich. This delightful café offers a cozy atmosphere, delectable treats, and a thoughtfully curated menu, ensuring a memorable visit.
host_about:
We turn temporarily vacant properties into contemporary furnished short-term rental apartments. 

Our apartments shall be functional and clean at a fair rate and our team can be reached 24/7 in order to assist you with anything you might need. 

Stay in our apartments without being guilty of contributing to gentrification. Our apartments are not being rented from the regular market to be let as furnished apartments. Properties we use are temporary empty and instead of staying empty are being furnished & rented to you for a limited amount of time.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.55 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is situated in a wealthy area of Zurich. The apartment is located to the small ancient "village center" which offers all daily supplies you need. On foot you are in "Niederdorf/old town zurich" in about 10min/1km). Museums like the museum of art or Kulturama (museum of culture) are in walking distance. Also theaters and the lake of Zurich are just a walk away. I strongly recommend to have a walk to Kafi Paradiesli, Hofstrasse 19, 8032 Zürich, a very nice sweet little hidden coffee place with a small but good menu.

host_about: I am an American expat in Switzerland having moved from New York City to Basel in 1991, then on to Zürich in 1996. I came to Airbnb several years back as a quasi co-host, working with a friend renting his apartment, and I realised how much I truly enjoyed meeting and welcoming people from all over the world. I have since traveled almost exclusively using Airbnb and feel that it is one of the few platforms that make it possible to personally connect with others.

Sicherheitskaution:
Bei Check-In benötigen wir eine Garantie über die Summe Ihres Aufenthaltes sowie CHF 200.00 für mögliche Extras als Sicherheitskaution. Nichtraucherhotel:
Das Rauchen ist in all unseren Hotelzimmern sowie in den öffentlichen Bereichen von THE FLAG Zürich strengstens untersagt. THE FLAG ist ein reines Nichtraucherhotel. Hotel- und Übernachtungsgäste haften für Schäden oder übermäßige Verschmutzung, welche sie am Eigentum von THE FLAG verursachen. Schadensersatzzahlungen werden mit der Sicherheitskaution verrechnet bzw. gesondert in Rechnung gestellt.

host_about:
"Home is where our story begins…"

And here is 'my' & 'our' story...

My journey to real estate entrepreneurship

As a global IT professional,  I came to Switzerland in 2007 to work for one of the two largest Swiss banks. 

And then began the hassle and cumbersome process to look for a rental apartment in Switzerland, which fits your budget and proximity to your work location.

I decided to do something to ease the hassles of finding an apartment for Expats in Switzerland.

Way back in 2014, a French co-guest in a hotel in Davos, suggested me to by an apartment which I can afford, instead of waiting for a dream house to buy.

And so began my first real estate entrepreneurial venture, when I  bought and rented my first apartment in Glattbrugg, Zürich in October 2014. 

In last 8 years, 'I' became 'WE' and we are making news as being among the first choice for global IT professionals for short or long term stay in Switzerland.

All our apartments are fully furnished with 101 + Items.

We do also support tourists in Zürich, Bern, Basel, Luzern, Lauterbrunnen and Zug.

We take pride in keeping the Indian tradition of valuing our guests as ´God´ - अतिथि देवो भवः (Atithi Devo Bhava) as we say in Sanskrit. It is our endeavour  to offer you a truly  ‘home-away-from-home’ experience, a feeling as someone rightly said. 

“Home is not a place…it’s a feeling.”

We believe in the philosophy ´the world is one family - वसुधैव कुटुम्बकम्  (Vasudhaiva Kutumbakam) and ´the global village´. 

It´s our  privilege and honor to welcome you from all over the world. I look forward to welcome you in our ´signature´ and beautifully done ´Swiss Home across Switzerland´.

You are welcome to choose from one of the  100 apartments all over Switzerland in all the different ´flavours´ - studio, sharing, holiday apartments, ladies only, sharing, full occupancy and even on daily and weekly basis.

We are the only one in Switzerland who gives you a ´home´. instead of an apartment and who connects you with ´community´ instead of just getting ´networked´ !

And we have a special offer for corporate travellers for long or short term stay in Switzerland and we provide invoices for all your stays.

Our beautifully done signature apartments all over Switzerland  ensure true feelings and warmth of ´home away´from home, a Swiss home with local ´flavour´!

Come, please enjoy our hospitality and spread the word around...

neighborhood_overview: Das Studio befindet sich im Stadtteil "Wipkingen". Ab und zu hört man den Begriff "Hipkingen" – was in einem Wort die Entwicklung der letzten 10-15 Jahre zusammenfasst. Das Quartier hat sich stark gewandelt und ist bei vielen Jungen und Familien sehr beliebt. Grünräume, Wald und vor allem der Fluss "Limmat" mit seinen Flussbädern ist sehr nahe gelegen. Gleichzeitig ist in den letzten Jahren ein grosses Angebot an kleinen Läden und Cafés entstanden. Dank dem Bahnhof Wipkingen ist das Gebiet sehr gut eingebunden und die Strecke zum Flughafen dauert tatsächlich nur 10 Minuten im Zug.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 2 baths
Rental unit in Zürich · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
District 1 is a very elegant part of town being the historic heart of the city which beats on both sides of the Limmat river.
The romantic little streets are lined by guild houses, churches and historic places.
The Old town with cobbled streets is full of cozy bars, traditional Swiss restaurants and art museums like the Kunsthaus.
Iconic churches include the Fraumünster with Chagall and Giacometti stained-glass windows. The luxurious shopping mile Bahnhofstrasse offers chocolate and jewelry stores next to high-end boutiques.
The popular Lindenhof hill offers views across the beautiful Limmat River with its famous promenade.

name: Serviced apartment in Zürich · ★5.0 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The apartments are located in the heart of the metropole of Zurich and in attractive proximity to the shore of Lake Zurich.

The "Seefeld" district is attractive for people who love city life, nature and the lake and is ideally located in Zurich's central banking and administrative district - just a few minutes' walk from the lake. As the most popular district for living and working, for leisure, culture and recreation, Seefeld is at the top of the agenda. Here you will find numerous neighbourhood shops, a wide range of restaurants from trendy to gourmet, fashionable boutiques, galleries and countless local recreational opportunities.

Hello! My name is Cher.

You are most welcome to come and stay in my unique apartments in Zurich, which have been prepared with you, the traveller in mind! The apartment will be your home away from home.

I will be very happy to give you recommendations during your stay, and I have prepared a bespoke Manual which upon check-in will give you useful information about the location, public transport and recommendations to restaurants and cafes in the neighbourhood, with clear directions how to get there from the apartment.

Der Kreis 7 gilt als Top-Wohnlage Zürichs. Er ist beliebt wegen der Ruhe, des Sonnenscheins und der schönen alten Bauten. Wer am Zürich- oder Adlisberg wohnt, hat hohe Ansprüche. Die Bauten werden gepflegt oder alte Bausubstanz durch Neubauten ersetzt.
Der Wald sowie diverse Parks bieten viel Platz für sportliche Aktivitäten oder für erholsame Stunden.
Für Kinder gibt es einen grossen Robinson-Spielplatz in nächster Nähe. Strand/Badeanstalten und Freibäder sind mit dem ÖV leicht erreichbar.
In der näheren Umgebung können Sie im Migros, Coop oder Denner gemütlich einkaufen oder ein Frühstück im Honold - Confiserie und Bäckerei - geniessen.

neighborhood_overview:
The area is nestled in the heart of the city, offering a vibrant and diverse neighbourhood with a blend of local cultures, traditions, and modern amenities.

It is rich in local cultures and traditions. The area is home to historical landmarks such as the Grossmünster, a magnificent Romanesque-style church, and the Fraumünster, famous for its stunning stained glass windows created by artist Marc Chagall. These architectural gems provide a glimpse into Zurich's history and cultural heritage.

Along the area and its adjacent streets, you'll find an array of charming boutique shops, upscale stores, and local businesses. Whether you're looking for fashionable clothing, Swiss watches, artisanal chocolates, or unique souvenirs, the neighbourhood offers a diverse range of shopping experiences to cater to various tastes and preferences.

host_about:
"Home is where our story begins…"

And here is 'my' & 'our' story...

My journey to real estate entrepreneurship

As a global IT professional,  I came to Switzerland in 2007 to work for one of the two largest Swiss banks. 

And then began the hassle and cumbersome process to look for a rental apartment in Switzerland, which fits your budget and proximity to your work location.

I decided to do something to ease the hassles of finding an apartment for Expats in Switzerland.

Way back in 2014, a French co-guest in a hotel in Davos, suggested me to by an apartment which I can afford, instead of waiting for a dream house to buy.

And so began my first real estate entrepreneurial venture, when I  bought and rented my first apartment in Glattbrugg, Zürich in October 2014. 

In last 8 years, 'I' became 'WE' and we are making news as being among the first choice for global IT professionals for short or long term stay in Switzerland.

All our apartments are fully furnished with 101 + Items.

We do also support tourists in Zürich, Bern, Basel, Luzern, Lauterbrunnen and Zug.

We take pride in keeping the Indian tradition of valuing our guests as ´God´ - अतिथि देवो भवः (Atithi Devo Bhava) as we say in Sanskrit. It is our endeavour  to offer you a truly  ‘home-away-from-home’ experience, a feeling as someone rightly said. 

“Home is not a place…it’s a feeling.”

We believe in the philosophy ´the world is one family - वसुधैव कुटुम्बकम्  (Vasudhaiva Kutumbakam) and ´the global village´. 

It´s our  privilege and honor to welcome you from all over the world. I look forward to welcome you in our ´signature´ and beautifully done ´Swiss Home across Switzerland´.

You are welcome to choose from one of the  100 apartments all over Switzerland in all the different ´flavours´ - studio, sharing, holiday apartments, ladies only, sharing, full occupancy and even on daily and weekly basis.

We are the only one in Switzerland who gives you a ´home´. instead of an apartment and who connects you with ´community´ instead of just getting ´networked´ !

And we have a special offer for corporate travellers for long or short term stay in Switzerland and we provide invoices for all your stays.

Our beautifully done signature apartments all over Switzerland  ensure true feelings and warmth of ´home away´from home, a Swiss home with local ´flavour´!

Come, please enjoy our hospitality and spread the word around...

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Our street has many high trees which reach partially up to the windows of the flat. So you see quite some green when you look down and you hear a lot birds singing. The street itself is narrow one-way street with little traffic in a residential area.

Within 5min walking you have 3 bakeries to choose from and several cafés. Also the public swimming areas of the river Limmat are just down the hill (8min walk) with a lot to explore and with further small restaurant/bar/coffee/wine places all along the river. Additionally to the "regular" food supermarkets close by there is also an organic food shop and a no-waste (packging free) organic shop within 15min walk away. The Farmers market (Tuesday+Friday) and the Fleamarket (Saturday) is 25min walk or 5min with the bus.

--> A list of my favorites you will find in the flat waiting for you :)

neighborhood_overview:
Unfortunately there is construction during weekdays and a construction site next-door. Post pandemic there are a lot of building projects that were delayed and are now in progress. Work starts at around 7am each morning and ends at 5. It's been fairly quiet lately but if you plan to work from the apartment everyday you might find the movement outside distracting.

The street is a little quiet at night, but a few blocks away in different directions you can find bars, restaurants, and cafes (including a daytime cafe across the street). There's a Coop supermarket one block away, and an Aldi and Migros 3-4 blocks away.

The Limmat river is only two blocks away for running paths and places to swim and sunbathe.

neighborhood_overview:
The lake is just 3 mins away!

The "Seefeld" district is attractive for people who love city life, nature and the lake and is ideally located in Zurich's central banking and administrative district - just a few minutes' walk from the lake. name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.67 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
Shopping: The Wiedikon area is full of shops like Coop (2 min from the door), Migros (6 min), Lidl (9 min). If you are into bio food, the Müller Reformhaus is also close. If you need anything else, the Sihlcity Center is only 10 min away from home or 2 with the bus. In a more oriental mood, there is the shop Alima (2 min), the Barkat (6 min), and if you like Asian food, the Lian Hua shop has an extensive choice.

Relaxation & Wellness: There is a beautiful path like a little forest behind our flat, it's leading to the very nice Kollerwiese parc. On the way there, you can find wild plants/fruits like blackberries, elderflower, cherries and nettle. The park is an amazing place to relax and recharge. The Fitnesspark Shilcity and the Zurich Thermal Baths are very close. There are also many gym and yoga offers in the area. Practical: There are pharmacies, a few ATM's, and the Post office is 10 min away from the flat, it's super practical.

N.

The Zürich Oerlikon train station is a major hub, making it easy to get around the city and further afield.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: Mühlebach is part of Zurich's eighth district and is located just east of Seefeld. The neighborhood is small in size, but offers a variety of attractions for locals and visitors alike. Cafe, bars and restaurants line Seefeldstrasse, with both Swiss and international cuisine on offer. Mühlebach is home to the venerable Heimatschutzzentrum in der Villa Patumbah, a gorgeous villa that has been converted into an architecture museum. Zurich's opera house is a short walk from the northern end of the neighborhood, and the lovely lakeside Chinagarten Zurich is an easy distance from the southern end. Mühlebach also has several smaller city parks all its own. The neighborhood is served by several bus and tram lines and has its own train station, Kreuzplatz.

neighborhood_overview: Set on the left bank of Lake Zurich, Wollishofen is a beautiful neighborhood that is prized for its twin waterside parks, Landiwiese and Saffa-Insel. This Central Zurich area is also known for great cuisine, including Irish pubs, casual spots catering to students and a variety of international restaurants and small shops. Other neighborhood highlights include the Rote Fabrik, a former factory that has been repurposed as a performing arts center, and the quirky Ortsmuseum Wollishofen. The incredible Reitberg Museum is just a short walk away from Wollishofen. The neighborhood is served by several bus, tram and S-Bahn lines, making it easy to get around.

name: Boutique hotel in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
host_about:
Das Alma Hotel befindet sich in ruhiger Lage im beliebten Seefeld Quartier, nur 100 m vom Zürichsee entfernt und in der Nähe mehrerer Strassenbahn- und Bushaltestellen. Das Opernhaus Zürich, das Bellevue sowie verschiedene Restaurants und Cafés befinden sich im Umkreis von 500 m. Den Zürich Hauptbahnhof erreicht man in 10 Fahrtminuten mit der Strassenbahn.
Die Stadtvilla aus dem 19. Jahrhundert besticht mit ihren 16 stillvollen und frisch renovierten Zimmern, sowie den 2 neuen Apartments, welche genügend Platz für Langzeitaufenthalter oder Familien bietet. Jedes Zimmer ist mit einem kleinen Schreibtisch, einem TV und einem Bad mit Dusche oder Wanne ausgestattet. Rollstuhlgerechte Zimmer stehen auf Anfrage ebenfalls zur Verfügung. WLAN nutzen Sie in allen Bereichen kostenfrei.
Ein reichhaltiges Frühstücksbuffet mit einer grossen Auswahl an frischen Broten, hausgemachten Müslis und frischen Säften wird Ihnen im Frühstücksraum angeboten. Italienische Speisen können von benachbarten Restaurant Amalfi bestellt werden.
Im exklusiv für Frauen zugänglichen Wellnessbereich erwarten Sie ein Dampfbad, eine Finnische- und eine Bio-Sauna. Grosse, beheizte Kirschkernkissen sind ebenfalls verfügbar. Auf der obersten Etage erwarten Sie ein Ruheraum sowie eine eigene wunderschöne Dachterrasse mit herrlicher Aussicht auf die Stadt, den See und die Berge.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: Cosmopolitan Langstrasse is part of Zürich's 4th district. Langstrasse is both the name of the neighborhood and its signature boulevard, which stretches from the city's district court house north to the Zürich Hauptbahnhof. Langstrasse is one of the city's most diverse neighborhoods, so it's no surprise that there is an abundance of international cuisine on offer. You can fill up on Mediterranean food at Schönau or sample Sichuan dishes at Khujug before living it up at one of the neighborhood's many cocktail lounges. Langstrasse is served by both bus and tram lines, and it's just a short walk to the nearest S-Bahn train station.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Unterstrass comprises part of Zurich's sixth district and stretches north from the city center. This vast area was an independent municipality before being incorporated into Zurich in 1893. The neighborhood is home to the Irchelpark campus of the University of Zurich -- not to be confused with Irchel Park, a lovely greenspace that is open to the public. Unterstrass is also the setting for Schindlergut and Beckenhof, two city parks that offer gorgeous Limmat views. There's a variety of both Swiss and international cuisine on offer, including Thai and Mexican food as well as pizza. Unterstrass is served by several bus and tram lines.

Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
host_about:
"Home is where our story begins…"

And here is 'my' & 'our' story...

My journey to real estate entrepreneurship

As a global IT professional,  I came to Switzerland in 2007 to work for one of the two largest Swiss banks. 

And then began the hassle and cumbersome process to look for a rental apartment in Switzerland, which fits your budget and proximity to your work location.

I decided to do something to ease the hassles of finding an apartment for Expats in Switzerland.

Way back in 2014, a French co-guest in a hotel in Davos, suggested me to by an apartment which I can afford, instead of waiting for a dream house to buy.

And so began my first real estate entrepreneurial venture, when I  bought and rented my first apartment in Glattbrugg, Zürich in October 2014. 

In last 8 years, 'I' became 'WE' and we are making news as being among the first choice for global IT professionals for short or long term stay in Switzerland.

All our apartments are fully furnished with 101 + Items.

We do also support tourists in Zürich, Bern, Basel, Luzern, Lauterbrunnen and Zug.

We take pride in keeping the Indian tradition of valuing our guests as ´God´ - अतिथि देवो भवः (Atithi Devo Bhava) as we say in Sanskrit. It is our endeavour  to offer you a truly  ‘home-away-from-home’ experience, a feeling as someone rightly said. 

“Home is not a place…it’s a feeling.”

We believe in the philosophy ´the world is one family - वसुधैव कुटुम्बकम्  (Vasudhaiva Kutumbakam) and ´the global village´. 

It´s our  privilege and honor to welcome you from all over the world. I look forward to welcome you in our ´signature´ and beautifully done ´Swiss Home across Switzerland´.

You are welcome to choose from one of the  100 apartments all over Switzerland in all the different ´flavours´ - studio, sharing, holiday apartments, ladies only, sharing, full occupancy and even on daily and weekly basis.

We are the only one in Switzerland who gives you a ´home´. instead of an apartment and who connects you with ´community´ instead of just getting ´networked´ !

And we have a special offer for corporate travellers for long or short term stay in Switzerland and we provide invoices for all your stays.

Our beautifully done signature apartments all over Switzerland  ensure true feelings and warmth of ´home away´from home, a Swiss home with local ´flavour´!

Come, please enjoy our hospitality and spread the word around...

neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

neighborhood_overview: Centrally located Werd may be small in size, but there's no shortage of things to do. The neighborhood is home to a thriving restaurant scene that encompasses both traditional Swiss food and the cuisine of Greece, Japan, Mexico, and more. There are also plenty of rollicking pubs and trendy bars like Kraftwerk, which serves coffee during the day and cocktails at night. Werd is home to the Museum Haus Konstruktiv, a converted power station that is now a showplace for contemporary art. There's also the quirky Jeans Museum and the Foundation FCZ Museum, an homage to the FC Zürich football team. Werd is served by several bus, tram and S-Bahn lines, and has two major train stations, Wiedikon and Selnau.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 1 bed · 1 bath
Rental unit in Zürich · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Located in Zurich's District 5 - a hip and vibrant part of town that invites you to stroll the streets and discover lesser known shops and restaurants serving all types of cuisine.

Tea or coffee? I'm a tea connoisseur (and my expansive tea selection is representative of that) but if you're a coffee lover, grab yourself a fresh brew at the Starbucks Sihlquai located just 1 minute from my apartment

Dine out at Europaallee (4 min walk), Zurich's newest part of town. Or, treat yourself to breakfast at the infamous Sprüngli at Paradeplatz (18 min walk / 7 min tram).

Jog or stroll along the Limmat river for whatever distance you desire. Also great for a refreshing dip with the locals on a hot summer's day.

Retail therapy needed? Explore Bahnhofstrasse (7 min walk), Niederdörfli (15 min walk) or Sihlcity (12 min train / 20 min tram).

Enjoy a trail - and the view - from Uetliberg, Zurich's own "mountain" (27 min train).
host_about: Born in Germany, I grew up in England and the USA and currently reside in Switzerland.  Inspired by the people I am lucky to meet from all walks of life while exploring this globe. Places and cultures are fascinating and rewarding.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The cosy and bright 2 room flat (70sqm) is located in the up-and-coming Oerlikon district: It is located directly at the transport hub of Oerlikon railway station. So, you can reach the international airport Kloten, the main station, the city centre including the beautiful Lake Zurich and all-important places in the city by public transport in a few minutes.
Various shopping facilities, restaurants and bars are only a few minutes' walk away. The Hallenstadion, where various major events such as trade fairs, concerts or sporting events take place, is only a 10-minute walk away.

Hello traveller,

I'm Swiss-Austrian and grew up in the Middle East. I'm in my thirties and love to travel, which I do as often possible. At home, I love brunching with friends, persuing my spiritual practice, ice swimming in the lake, philosophising over theater and the world,  exploring flea markets and exhibitions and anything wonder related.

I wish for all of us to stay curious and keep discovering this vibrant world. Maybe meet you soon?
Great greetings,
Felicitas

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Busy Oerlikon is a convenient neighborhood in the northern part of Zürich where there's no shortage of things to do. One important landmark is the Hallenstadion, an arena that hosts concerts and sports events. Other local highlights include the Kunsteisbahn Oerlikon skating rink and Theater 11 Zürich, where you can catch a traveling Broadway show. The neighborhood is also the setting for the city's sprawling Messe Zürich exhibition center, a busy meeting space that's surrounded by a variety of shops and restaurants. The Zürich Oerlikon train station is a major hub, making it easy to get around the city and further afield.

neighborhood_overview:
Langstrasse is Zurich's most colorful and diverse quarter. During the day you can enjoy international specialties and multicultural shopping opportunities here, while at night the street mutates into Zurich's nightlife.

One bar follows the other, hip clubs are at home here and if you get hungry from partying, you can get food in many take-aways and 24-hour shops.

Langstrasse never sleeps and has advanced from being a red-light district to one of the city's most popular areas. This is also thanks to the many young designers and restaurateurs who have upgraded the quarter in recent years.

Dear future guests,

I love travelling, so I’m often absent. For me, the best way to get to know a city is by living there like a local person, and this can only be done, of course, by getting accommodation. It is with this in mind that whenever I am travelling, I make my lodging facility available to travelers from around the world, so: why not you?

Don’t worry, even if I’m not present when you are doing the booking arrangement, Luckey, Airbnb’s official concierge, to whom I have entrusted the management of my home, will make your stay as enjoyable as possible!

See you soon,

Laurent.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: Set on the left bank of Lake Zurich, Wollishofen is a beautiful neighborhood that is prized for its twin waterside parks, Landiwiese and Saffa-Insel. This Central Zurich area is also known for great cuisine, including Irish pubs, casual spots catering to students and a variety of international restaurants and small shops. Other neighborhood highlights include the Rote Fabrik, a former factory that has been repurposed as a performing arts center, and the quirky Ortsmuseum Wollishofen. The incredible Reitberg Museum is just a short walk away from Wollishofen. The neighborhood is served by several bus, tram and S-Bahn lines, making it easy to get around.

Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Just southeast of central Zurich is Weinegg, a sprawling, semi-rural district set on a wooden hillside far above the city. This peaceful area is an easy introduction to the city, with plenty of conveniences. There are also notable cultural attractions, including Zurich's Tram Museum, where you can see decommissioned cars from the 19th and 20th centuries, and the University of Zurich Botanical Gardens, where you can explore the world of plants. Wine lovers will want to save time on the weekends to explore the various vineyards set in the hills of Weinegg. The neighborhood is served by several bus, tram and S-Bahn lines, making it easy to get around.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Historic Altstetten is part of Zürich's 9th district, and there is plenty to do and see. The neighborhood is home to a variety of bars and restaurants as well as several high-end international hotels. Altstetten was once a city in its own right, but was incorporated into Zürich proper in 1934. Nearby highlights include the Museum für Gestaltung Zürich, where you can marvel at 19th and 20th century posters and everyday design objects, and the Schweizer Finanzmuseum. Altstetten is served by several IR train lines.

The rooms are newly renovated, they all have a sink in the room, toilets and showers are shared.
It's an almost 500-year-old building with a lot of charm. 
***
Einmalige Lage, direkt am Limmatquai im Herzen von Zürich. Nur 7 Gehminuten vom Hauptbahnhof entfernt, Tramhaltestelle »Rudolf-Brun-Brücke» direkt vor dem Haus.
Frisch renovierte und neu eingerichtete Zimmer, alle mit Lavabo im Zimmer, Duschen/Toiletten auf dem Gang. 
Schöner Aufenthaltsraum mit Blick auf die Limmat. Ein 500-jähriges Haus mit viel Charme!

You’ll find a range of local shops, supermarkets, and cozy cafes, creating a vibrant community feel. Friesenberg also offers cultural experiences with its proximity to museums, art galleries, and diverse dining options. Whether you seek a serene retreat or convenient access to urban amenities, Friesenberg is the perfect choice. Immerse yourself in tranquility, explore green spaces, and savor local flavors. Friesenberg is an idyllic haven within dynamic Zürich, offering a unique experience for residents and visitors alike.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Just southeast of central Zurich is Weinegg, a sprawling, semi-rural district set on a wooden hillside far above the city. This peaceful area is an easy introduction to the city, with plenty of conveniences. There are also notable cultural attractions, including Zurich's Tram Museum, where you can see decommissioned cars from the 19th and 20th centuries, and the University of Zurich Botanical Gardens, where you can explore the world of plants. Wine lovers will want to save time on the weekends to explore the various vineyards set in the hills of Weinegg. The neighborhood is served by several bus, tram and S-Bahn lines, making it easy to get around.

host_about:
Hello world! 

I very much enjoy travelling and getting to know other cultures and its people. While seeing tourist attractions is definitely fun and interesting, I am also very enthusiastic about meeting locals. A good chat or a night out can be the most insightful thing;) 

I am very international myself. I am half-Thai, half-German born and raised in Bavaria (Würzburg). Having spent a high school year in the USA (Seattle), I chose to study at the international Jacobs University Bremen, where only a quarter of the students is German. I finished my BSc in Physics there and continued my studies at the ETH Zürich, Switzerland. Now I live between Zurich, working as an AI Consultant, and Bangkok, working as teacher for Data Science.

I am very open-minded and always up for a talk about pretty much anything, not only physics;) In my free time I enjoy sports in general but especially football, dancing and electronic music.

Looking forward to meeting you!

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.62 · 3 bedrooms · 4 beds · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Die Langstrasse ist Zürichs buntestes und vielfältigstes Quartier. Tagsüber geniesst man hier internationale Spezialitäten und multikulturelle Einkaufsmöglichkeiten, während die Strasse in der Nacht zu Zürichs Ausgangsmeile mutiert.

Eine Bar reiht sich an die andere, angesagte Clubs sind hier beheimatet und wenn man vom Feiern Hunger bekommt, kann man sich in vielen Take Aways und 24-Stunden-Shops mit Essen versorgen.

Die Langstrasse schläft nie und ist vom ehemaligen Rotlichtmilieu zu einem der beliebtesten Viertel der Stadt avanciert. Dies auch dank vieler junger Designer und Gastronomen, die das Quartier in den letzten Jahren aufgewertet haben.
(Text zuerich.com)
host_about:
Unique location, directly on Limmatquai in the heart of Zurich's old town. Only 7 minutes by foot to the train station, a tram stop is just outside the building (»Rudolf-Brun-Brücke»). 
The rooms are newly renovated, they all have a sink in the room, toilets and showers are shared.
It's an almost 500-year-old building with a lot of charm. 
***
Einmalige Lage, direkt am Limmatquai im Herzen von Zürich. Nur 7 Gehminuten vom Hauptbahnhof entfernt, Tramhaltestelle »Rudolf-Brun-Brücke» direkt vor dem Haus.
Frisch renovierte und neu eingerichtete Zimmer, alle mit Lavabo im Zimmer, Duschen/Toiletten auf dem Gang. 
Schöner Aufenthaltsraum mit Blick auf die Limmat. Ein 500-jähriges Haus mit viel Charme!

neighborhood_overview: Just southeast of central Zurich is Weinegg, a sprawling, semi-rural district set on a wooden hillside far above the city. This peaceful area is an easy introduction to the city, with plenty of conveniences. There are also notable cultural attractions, including Zurich's Tram Museum, where you can see decommissioned cars from the 19th and 20th centuries, and the University of Zurich Botanical Gardens, where you can explore the world of plants. Wine lovers will want to save time on the weekends to explore the various vineyards set in the hills of Weinegg. The neighborhood is served by several bus, tram and S-Bahn lines, making it easy to get around.

neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

neighborhood_overview:
Offene, grosszügige Dachwohnung in super lebendigem Viertel in Zürich (Wipkingen–Schaffhauser Platz). In direkter Nähe befinden sich mehrere Cafes, Bars, Restaurants und Supermärkte. Die Limmat ist nur knapp 10 Minuten zu Fuss entfernt und lädt im Sommer zum Baden ein.
Zum Hauptbahnhof fährt die Tram vom Schaffhauser Platz in weniger als 10 Minuten, zum Flughafen bringt dich die S-Bahn vom Bahnhof Wipkingen ebenfalls in 10 Minuten.
Ein schöner Spaziergang führt dich in ca. einer halben Std durch einen Park und am Fluss entlang in die Innenstadt. In der anderen Richtung erreichst du nach 10 Gehminuten den Käferberg mit Wald, von dem aus du einen tollen Blick über die ganze Stadt hast.

Our apartment is based on the first floor in a quiet neighbourhood, but very close to bus/tram stops, small convenience shops and 15 mins away from the mainstation.
The river limmat is only 10 minutes walk away and perfect to go jogging. For more sports you can go up the hill for 20 minutes where you find a Vitaparcours (sports parcours) in the forest.

Wipkingen is a part of Zürich that changes more and more into a hip place. I recommend a typical Swiss brunch at "Kafi Schnaps" or "Restaurant Nordbrücke".

Just on the other side of the river you find the new emerging "Zürich West" with many bars, clubs, restaurants and the Prime Tower (tallest building of Zürich with restaurant/lounge on the top).

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Seefeld ist ein Quartier in der Stadt Zürich im Kreis 8 (Riesbach), am rechten Ufer des Zürichsees gelegen.
Sehenswürdigkeiten sind die grosszügigen Park- und Quaianlagen mit verschiedenen Skulpturen (u. a. Heureka von Jean Tinguely und Sheep Piece von Henry Moore), dem Chinagarten und dem letzten vom Architekten Le Corbusier entworfenen Gebäude. Weiter zu erwähnen sind die beiden Seebäder Tiefenbrunnen und Utoquai, der Botanische Garten und die alten Villen sowie die Mühle Tiefenbrunnen, eine ehemalige Bierbrauerei und Mühle, die heute als Kultur- und Begegnungszentrum genutzt wird.

Im Seefeld findet man überdurchschnittlich viele Feinkostgeschäfte, Friseure und Anwaltskanzleien. Als Wohnquartier ist das Seefeld sehr beliebt, aber auch dementsprechend teuer. Das Seefeld ist auch das Schweizer Quartier mit dem höchsten Anteil von Akademikern an der Wohnbevölkerung (70 %).

Mit dem FC Seefeld Zürich ist das Quartier in der 1. Liga, der dritthöchsten Spielklasse

There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Set on the left bank of Lake Zurich, Wollishofen is a beautiful neighborhood that is prized for its twin waterside parks, Landiwiese and Saffa-Insel. This Central Zurich area is also known for great cuisine, including Irish pubs, casual spots catering to students and a variety of international restaurants and small shops. Other neighborhood highlights include the Rote Fabrik, a former factory that has been repurposed as a performing arts center, and the quirky Ortsmuseum Wollishofen. The incredible Reitberg Museum is just a short walk away from Wollishofen. The neighborhood is served by several bus, tram and S-Bahn lines, making it easy to get around.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.77 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
In unmittelbaren Umgebung gibt es zahlreiche Bars und Restaurants, die für jeden Geschmack etwas zu bieten haben.
 
Die Lage der Wohnung ist ideal, um die Stadt zu erkunden. Vor dem Haus gibt es zahlreiche Parkplätze für Ihr Auto. Die Polyterrasse, die den spektakulärsten Blick über die Stadt bietet, ist nur 5 Gehminuten entfernt. Der Zürichsee und die Limmat befinden sich ebenfalls in unmittelbarer Nähe und bieten zahlreiche Freizeitmöglichkeiten wie Spazierengehen, Radfahren und Bootfahren.
 
Ein weiteres Highlight ist der TOP of Zurich Uetliberg, der mit der S-Bahn vom Hauptbahnhof Zürich in nur 20 Minuten erreichbar ist. Der Blick von hier oben auf die Stadt ist einfach unvergesslich!
 
Alles in allem bietet dieses Apartment alles, was man für einen unvergesslichen Aufenthalt in Zürich braucht. Die perfekte Lage, die stilvolle Einrichtung und die atemberaubende Aussicht machen es zum perfekten Ort für Ihren nächsten Urlaub. Buchen Sie jetzt und lassen

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: Cosmopolitan Langstrasse is part of Zürich's 4th district. Langstrasse is both the name of the neighborhood and its signature boulevard, which stretches from the city's district court house north to the Zürich Hauptbahnhof. Langstrasse is one of the city's most diverse neighborhoods, so it's no surprise that there is an abundance of international cuisine on offer. You can fill up on Mediterranean food at Schönau or sample Sichuan dishes at Khujug before living it up at one of the neighborhood's many cocktail lounges. Langstrasse is served by both bus and tram lines, and it's just a short walk to the nearest S-Bahn train station.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
District east of the Zurich city centre on a hillside of hill 'Zürichberg', often with fantastic lake view.

Preferred, partially upscale residential area with beautiful renovated old buildings and villas, often with gardens.

Good shopping possibilities, recreational area by the hill Adlisberg, attractive Zurich zoo, swimming pools on Tobelhofstrasse & Dolder, skating rink Dolder, tennis courts by the Adlisberg & Sonnenberg. Near Lycée Français de Zurich in Gockhausen and Dolder golfing grounds. Private clinic Bethanien, Red Cross hospital, children's hospital.

neighborhood_overview: Enge is nestled between the Limmat River and Lake Zürich, and the neighborhood is part of Zürich's 2nd district. This tiny area packs in a lot to see and do. Enge is home to the FIFA World Football Museum and the Museum Rietberg, a 19th century villa that now displays non-European artworks. There are also several parks to enjoy: heavily landscaped Reiter Park recalls the glamor of a bygone age while lakeside Belvoirpark is perfect for a picnic or morning jog. You can find everything from fast food to traditional Swiss cuisine to sushi in Enge. The neighborhood is served by several bus and tram lines as well as Zürich's S-Bahn trains.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.86 · 3 bedrooms · 4 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is just round the corner from Stauffacher, and close to Zurich’s vibrant central district. Surrounded by restaurants, shops and services, this neighbourhood is safe and has plenty to offer.

With many popular restaurants just right next door (Ichizen Japanese, Mythos Greek, Molino Italian, Le Cedre Lebanese, St. Jakob Bakery & Café etc.) and a mini supermarket just one minute walk away, you are well served in the area.

For those who like to keep active, NON STOP GYM is right across the road and Hallenbad City Indoor Swimming Pool is within five minutes of the apartment, while nearby Kasernenareal Park is perfect for a lunchtime stroll.

And if you’re keen to soak up some culture, the Kantonspolizei Zürich Kriminalmuseum and Haus Konstruktiv modern art museum are all a short walk away.
host_about:
Hello! My name is Cher.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Alstad is the city's 1st district, and represented the entirety of Zürich until 1893 -- fitting, since the name means "old town" in German. This centrally located neighborhood is home to the Swiss National Museum and the Zürich Opera House as well as the Schauspielhaus Zürich, one of the most important theaters in the German-speaking world. Alstad is the perfect place to sample traditional Swiss cuisine at restaurants like Zeughauskeller, where you can dine in a beautifully restored 15th century arsenal. You can also shop for chocolate, jewelry, and designer wares along the Bahnhofstrasse. Alstad is quite walkable, and there are ferries, trams, and S-Bahn trains for when you want to venture further afield.
