name: Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Historic Altstetten is part of Zürich's 9th district, and there is plenty to do and see. The neighborhood is home to a variety of bars and restaurants as well as several high-end international hotels. Altstetten was once a city in its own right, but was incorporated into Zürich proper in 1934. Nearby highlights include the Museum für Gestaltung Zürich, where you can marvel at 19th and 20th century posters and everyday design objects, and the Schweizer Finanzmuseum. Altstetten is served by several IR train lines.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.
host_about:

With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer.

neighborhood_overview: Historic Altstetten is part of Zürich's 9th district, and there is plenty to do and see. The neighborhood is home to a variety of bars and restaurants as well as several high-end international hotels. Altstetten was once a city in its own right, but was incorporated into Zürich proper in 1934. Nearby highlights include the Museum für Gestaltung Zürich, where you can marvel at 19th and 20th century posters and everyday design objects, and the Schweizer Finanzmuseum. Altstetten is served by several IR train lines.

Sihlcity, which is a big department store with anything from groceries to Zara, and 5 mind away there is the Migros at Bahnhof Enge which is also open on Sundays. Great co-working option also at Bahnhof Enge as well as Coffee Shops and Restaurants.

name: Hotel in Zürich · ★4.67 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 private bath
host_about:
Lieber Gast,

herzlichen Dank für Ihr Interesse an unserem Unternehmen THE FLAG Zürich. Damit Sie sich auch in Zeiten von Corona sicher und wohl während Ihres Aufenthalts bei uns fühlen, möchten wir Ihnen im Folgenden einige Hinweise geben.
Wir möchten Sie darauf aufmerksam machen, dass aufgrund der aktuellen Coronapandemie in unserem Hotel eine strenge Maskenpflicht gilt. Bitte Tragen Sie eine Maske, sobald Sie Ihr Hotelzimmer verlassen und sich in öffentlichen Bereichen (Lobby, Flur, Aufzug, Tiefgarage etc.) aufhalten. Die Maske muss immer die Nase und den Mund bedecken.

Darüber hinaus möchten wir Sie darauf hinweisen, dass sich stets nur die bei der Buchung angegebene Anzahl an Personen in den Hotelzimmern aufhalten darf. Der Aufenthalt von weiteren Personen, Besuch oder Ähnlichem ist nicht gestattet. Wir behalten uns vor, unser Hausrecht bei Zuwiderhandlung (notfalls polizeilich) geltend zu machen. Feiern, Partys oder ähnliche Ansammlungen in den Hotelzimmern sind strengstens verboten. 

Sicherheitskaution:
Bei Check-In benötigen wir eine Garantie über die Summe Ihres Aufenthaltes sowie CHF 200.00 für mögliche Extras als Sicherheitskaution. Diese kann bei Anreise in Form von Bargeld, EC- oder Kreditkarte hinterlegt werden. Eine Rückerstattung erfolgt unmittelbar nach Ihrer Abreise. Das Hotel kann zudem eine Kopie Ihres Ausweises anfertigen.

Nichtraucherhotel:
Das Rauchen ist in all unseren Hotelzimmern sowie in den öffentlichen Bereichen von THE FLAG Zürich strengstens untersagt. THE FLAG ist ein reines Nichtraucherhotel. Bei Verstoß gegen das Rauchverbot behalten wir uns vor, die Reinigungskosten (bis zu CHF 500.00) in Rechnung zu stellen bzw. mit der Sicherheitskaution zu verrechnen. Das Rauchen ist nur auf Balkonen und Terrassen erlaubt.

Sachbeschädigung und Haftung:
Hotel- und Übernachtungsgäste haften für Schäden oder übermäßige Verschmutzung, welche sie am Eigentum von THE FLAG verursachen. Schadensersatzzahlungen werden mit der Sicherheitskaution verrechnet bzw. gesondert in Rechnung gestellt. 

Nachtruhe:
Zwischen 22.00 und 07.00 Uhr bitten wir Sie, die Nachtruhe zu respektieren und andere Gäste nicht zu stören. Personen, die gegen die Hausruhe verstoßen, kann ein weiterer Aufenthalt im THE FLAG Zürich verweigert werden. Ebenfalls kann ein Hausverbot ausgesprochen werden.


Zuwiderhandlungen gegen die vorgenannten Regeln werden mit bis zu CHF 500.00 geahndet.

Vielen Dank für die Beachtung der Regeln. Sollten Sie Fragen zu Ihrem Aufenthalt haben, stehen wir Ihnen jederzeit gerne zur Verfügung.

Wir würden uns freuen, Sie bald als Gast begrüßen zu dürfen und wünschen Ihnen bis dahin noch eine schöne Zeit!  

Herzlichst,
Ihr THE FLAG Zürich Team

neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to the charming and verdant Kreis 2 neighborhood of Zurich, situated on the left bank of Lake Zurich.

For those seeking activities and attractions in Zurich, this is the places to be. With its lush greenery, Kreis 2 is often referred to as the "lung of the city." From the Entlisberg and Leimbach forests to the Mythenquai city pool, there are plenty of green spaces to explore. For a cozy picnic or a morning yoga session, I recommends the Rieterpark, which is home to the Rietberg Museum and its impressive collection of non-European art.

Vintage lovers will find paradise at Barbar Vintage, a store that has been around since 1974. Previously located in Niederdörfli, the shop is now conveniently located near the Enge train station. Here, you can find a well-curated selection of vintage fashion.

neighborhood_overview: Unterstrass comprises part of Zurich's sixth district and stretches north from the city center. This vast area was an independent municipality before being incorporated into Zurich in 1893. The neighborhood is home to the Irchelpark campus of the University of Zurich -- not to be confused with Irchel Park, a lovely greenspace that is open to the public. Unterstrass is also the setting for Schindlergut and Beckenhof, two city parks that offer gorgeous Limmat views. There's a variety of both Swiss and international cuisine on offer, including Thai and Mexican food as well as pizza. Unterstrass is served by several bus and tram lines.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment location is a charming old-town of Zurich. The area is home to many historical landmarks, trendy shops, and restaurants that cater to different tastes and preferences.

The local culture in the area is rich and diverse, with many festivals and celebrations throughout the year. Visitors can enjoy the traditional Swiss culture and customs, including the famous Swiss chocolate, cheese fondue, and Alpine horn music.

For those who enjoy outdoor activities, the neighbourhood has plenty to offer. There are several parks and green spaces, including the beautiful Lindenhof Hill Park, where you can take a stroll or have a picnic while enjoying the stunning views of the city.

Another popular outdoor activity is walking along the Limmat River, which runs through the heart of the city. Visitors can rent bikes or take a boat tour to explore the river and its surroundings.

The neighbourhood also offers plenty of great spots for food and drink.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Unterstrass comprises part of Zurich's sixth district and stretches north from the city center. This vast area was an independent municipality before being incorporated into Zurich in 1893. The neighborhood is home to the Irchelpark campus of the University of Zurich -- not to be confused with Irchel Park, a lovely greenspace that is open to the public. Unterstrass is also the setting for Schindlergut and Beckenhof, two city parks that offer gorgeous Limmat views. There's a variety of both Swiss and international cuisine on offer, including Thai and Mexican food as well as pizza. Unterstrass is served by several bus and tram lines.

name: Hotel in Zürich · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
Rental unit in Zürich · ★4.63 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the Seefeld district of Zurich, is known for its vibrant and trendy atmosphere. The area is filled with trendy cafes, restaurants, and bars, making it a popular spot for locals and tourists alike.

The Seefeld district is home to a mix of cultures, with a strong presence of expats and international students. This creates a diverse and cosmopolitan atmosphere, where you can experience a variety of local and international cultures.

There are plenty of shops and boutiques in the area, ranging from high-end designer stores to local artisan shops. The Seefeld district is also known for its outdoor activities, with nearby parks and the beautiful Lake Zurich just a short walk away.

If you're looking for some traditional Swiss cuisine, there are plenty of options in the neighborhood, including classic Swiss fondue and raclette restaurants. You can also find a variety of international cuisines, from Japanese sushi to Italian pasta.

neighborhood_overview: Serene Wipkingen is one of the quarters of Zürich's tenth district. Set along the Limmat River, this dynamic area is ideal for new arrivals to the city. There are a variety of cafes, bars and restaurants near the riverbank, including everything from regional French cuisine to pizza to Indian barbecue. There is also a supermarket in Wipkingen for anyone who prefers to self cater. Several museums, including the National Finance Museum, and a cinema are a short walk from Wipkingen. The neighborhood is served by several tram and bus lines as well as local and regional rail from Zürich Wipkingen train station.

neighborhood_overview: Hip Escher Wyss is set along the left bank of the Limmat. This formerly industrial neighborhood is now a hotspot for young people, thanks to its nightlife scene and proximity to Zurich University of the Arts. Whether you love sports bars, breweries, clubs, or swanky cocktail bars, you'll find your new favorite watering hole night in the area. Escher Wyss also has a cinema, and you can shop for the latest fashions on Viaduktstrasse. The neighborhood's cultural highlights include the Museum of Digital Art, the Migros Museum für Gegenwartskunst and the Kunsthalle Zürich, a contemporary art museum set within a converted brewery. Escher Wyss is served by several bus and tram lines.

neighborhood_overview:
Get ready for a lively, fun-filled stay! Our apartment nestles in Zurich Seefeld, one of the most beautiful and serene neighborhoods of Zurich, a city celebrated globally for its unmatched quality of life, as attested by prestigious publications like Monocle.

Just steps away, you'll find the stunning Zurich Lake. This local gem is fringed with restaurants that float on and border the lake, making dining an unforgettable experience. Enjoy a meal while being cradled by gentle waves, or select a charming spot on the shore for an al fresco feast.

The area is dotted with adorable outdoor cafes, perfect for sipping a latte while people-watching. Adventurous souls can enjoy a stand-up paddleboard session on the lake or even dive under its serene surface for an aquatic adventure. And, of course, there's a spacious park nearby where you can set up your own barbecue and soak in the ambiance.

The neighborhood truly comes alive in the summer with grand festivities

neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

Kulturliebhaber kommen im Opernhaus, im Schauspielhaus und im Kunsthaus voll auf ihre Kosten. It’s a lively neighbourhood but quiet after 8pm.
Everything is just downstairs: supermarkets, bakery, bio shops, pharmacy, post office, bank, hair salon, restaurants, bars…

Surrounded by nature, with parks, vineyards, forest.

Just 10 mins walking to the beaches on the Limmat river, where you can swim in clean water or picnic on the grass.

2 bus stops from ETH university

8 mins to Escher Wyss Platz
(with bars, cinemas, and the contemporary art district, Löwenbräu-Kunst with galleries/museums).

5 mins bus to a beautiful swimming pool with warm water

neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

host_about:
Welcome to Marc's beautiful properties on Airbnb! Marc, also known as "The Godfather," and Tallulah, the property manager, are thrilled to offer you several options for your stay.

The first property is a cozy chalet located in Stoos, Schwyz. Nestled in the mountains, this charming retreat offers stunning views, rustic furnishings, and all the amenities you need to enjoy a comfortable stay. Whether you're looking to hit the slopes or simply escape the hustle and bustle of city life, this chalet is the perfect place to unwind.

The second property is a beautiful manor located in Riehen, Basel. This grand estate features several rooms available for rent, each one tastefully decorated and fully equipped with everything you need for a comfortable stay. The manor is in close proximity to the Beyeler Foundation museum in Riehen, which is widely considered the best museum in Switzerland. Additionally, the famous Basel Exhibition Square hosts several grand events throughout the year and is easily accessible from the manor.

One of the rooms in the Riehen manor is the Hermann Hesse room, where the renowned writer himself used to stay. This room offers a unique historical experience, allowing guests to immerse themselves in the atmosphere of one of Switzerland's most beloved literary figures.

Whether you choose to stay in the cozy mountain chalet in Stoos or one of the elegant rooms in the Riehen manor, you'll be greeted with warm hospitality from Marc and Tallulah. They take great pride in providing their guests with a memorable experience, and are always available to assist with any needs or questions you may have.

So why wait?

 Book your stay at one of Marc's beautiful properties on Airbnb today, and get ready to experience the very best that these amazing properties have to offer!

neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

neighborhood_overview: Seefeld is situated along the east bank of Lake Zürich, and the neighborhood comprises part of the city's 8th district. The best part of living in this area is the gorgeous lakeside promenade. You can picnic, swim, and enjoy Alpine views at Zürichhorn, a lovely park. Another popular attraction is Chinagarten Zürich, a lakeside garden with Chinese pavilions and plantings. Seefeld has an interesting food scene, with everything from casual outdoor dining with lake views to traditional Italian on offer. There are also cocktail bars and coffee houses where you can kick back and relax. Seefeld is served by several bus and tram lines as well as Zürich's S-Bahn train system.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in Zurich's Oerlikon district, a community that harmoniously blends local culture, modern conveniences, and a vibrant atmosphere. Here's a glimpse of the neighborhood:

Diverse Cultural Blend:
Oerlikon's residents, a diverse mix of local and international individuals, contribute to its rich cultural tapestry. While it may lack the historical charm of Zurich's Old Town, Oerlikon offers a contemporary Swiss urban experience, merging Swiss efficiency with a cosmopolitan lifestyle.

Shopping Options:
The neighborhood hosts a range of shops, from supermarkets to boutiques and specialty stores, catering to everyday needs and offering unique Swiss products.

Dining Experiences:
Oerlikon spoils you for choice with its array of bars and restaurants serving Swiss and international cuisine, as well as trendy dining options. Explore Swiss classics like fondue and raclette or embark on a global culinary journey.

Outdo

name: Rental unit in Zürich · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

neighborhood_overview: Busy Oerlikon is a convenient neighborhood in the northern part of Zürich where there's no shortage of things to do. One important landmark is the Hallenstadion, an arena that hosts concerts and sports events. neighborhood_overview: Wiedikon is Zurich's third district, and has a residential character. This quiet neighborhood is set on the lower slopes of Uetliberg, which makes for some incredible views. There are also hiking trails nearby, including the Planet Trail, an easy two hour hike from Uetliberg to Felsenegg. Wiedikon is home to a variety of restaurants, encompassing everything from fast casual dining to traditional Swiss fare. The Sihlcity shopping mall is the perfect place to indulge in some retail therapy, and the surrounding area is home to cocktail lounges and pubs, as well as several notable international restaurants. There are train stations and tram stops throughout Wiedikon, making it easy to get into the heart of the city quickly.

neighborhood_overview: Enge is nestled between the Limmat River and Lake Zürich, and the neighborhood is part of Zürich's 2nd district. This tiny area packs in a lot to see and do. Enge is home to the FIFA World Football Museum and the Museum Rietberg, a 19th century villa that now displays non-European artworks. There are also several parks to enjoy: heavily landscaped Reiter Park recalls the glamor of a bygone age while lakeside Belvoirpark is perfect for a picnic or morning jog. You can find everything from fast food to traditional Swiss cuisine to sushi in Enge. The neighborhood is served by several bus and tram lines as well as Zürich's S-Bahn trains.

neighborhood_overview:
You live in the contrasting and beautiful district of Höngg, directly on the banks of the Limmat with a unique view. Just a few minutes' walk away is every Zurich resident's insider tip: Werdinsel, which invites you to take long walks and, in summer, enjoy a swim. A footpath runs along the Limmat, which is perfect for a morning jog or simply a nice walk.

The "Winzerhalde" bus stop is right next to the accommodation. This means you can easily get to the neighboring districts or the center of Zurich by bus. The world-famous ETH Hönggerberg university is also just a quarter of an hour away.
host_about:
Hey ich bin Patrick und wohne mit meiner Frau und meinen zwei Jungs in einem Vorort von Zürich. Meine Frau sagt immer, dass ich ein Social Butterfly sei, was ich bestätigen kann.
Ich freue mich jedenfalls, wenn ich dir als Gast in meiner Unterkunft ein tolles Erlebnis und schöne Erinnerungen bieten darf. Da wir selbst gerne umherreisen, weiss ich genau, wie wichtig das ist.

The comfortable furnished apartments of PABS Résidences + Appartements AG in central Zurich can be easily booked within few minutes. Their comfort is very attractive, the rents are fair and "all inclusive". For 26 years now, PABS Résidences + Appartments AG has been helping private and corporate clients find furnished apartments and residences to rent in the centre of Zurich. PABS Résidences + Appartements AG is also the leading contact for relocation companies and people who are moving to Zurich temporarily.

Beautiful and modern furnished apartments in the heart of Zurich
If you plan to stay in Zurich for longer than 14 days, you can browse through our 250 low-priced apartments on this home page under "Apartment search".

Comfortable, furnished rental apartments: great value to suit your every need:
A wide range of apartments in the Zurich city centre and all central city districts.
Full service with a central, competent contact person for advice, reservations, rental contracts, check-in and check-out.
Booking, checking in and checking out all take just a few minutes – saving you plenty of time.
All-inclusive, first-rate services (weekly cleaning thanks to our cleaning staff, repair service, emergency service 24/24).
Information is constantly updated. Simply download the iOS App or follow our social media pages (see links on this page).
With its wide selection of 250 furnished apartments in Zurich, PABS Résidences und Appartements AG offers you a great deal of choice. The standard minimum rental period for furnished apartments is one month. A furnished apartment is usually available for last minute bookings for rental periods of 14 days or longer.

At PABS Ltd., we provide you with comprehensive information and a list of furnished apartments in Zurich with plenty of great value offers (by telephone or email). Our standard apartments include: a modern, well-equipped kitchen, TV, appliances and household infrastructure as well as fresh sheets and towels. The rental price for all apartments includes the costs for electricity, water and heating, TV, weekly cleaning and laundry service.

Our top priority at PABS Ltd. is making sure that our clients are satisfied with the apartments they rent.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★New · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
host_about:
Our real estate company is a leading provider of serviced apartments solutions, dedicated to delivering exceptional services to our clients. With a focus on providing high-quality, fully-furnished apartments that offer all the comforts of home, we have become a trusted name in the industry.

We specialize in providing serviced apartments that are ideal for both short-term and long-term stays, and we offer a range of options to meet the unique needs of each client. From luxury apartments in prime locations to more affordable options, we have something to suit every budget and preference.

Our team of experienced professionals is dedicated to providing exceptional service and ensuring that our clients have a seamless and enjoyable experience. We understand that our clients have busy lives, and we are committed to making their stay with us as comfortable and convenient as possible.

Whether you are a corporate traveler, a family on vacation, or anyone in between, we are here to provide you with the perfect serviced apartment solution. With a focus on quality and service, we are dedicated to ensuring that our clients have the best possible experience, every time.

name: Home in Zürich · ★New · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
host_about:
Hey, bin ein sehr unternehmungslustiger und lebensfroher Mensch, Yogalehrerin, Sängerin surfe + snowboarde unglaublich gerne und reise sehr viel. 
In meinem Alltag fahre ich sehr gerne mit dem Fahrrad zur Uni oder wohin auch immer ich muss und daher möchte ich sehr gerne mein Auto anderen genauso abenteuerlustigen Menschen zur Verfügung stellen. 

Mein Minivan eignet sich perfekt für kurze Trips um den Bodensee herum, hat ein eingebautes 140x2m Bett - daher großer Schlafkomfort und es gibt auch einen Kleinen Kocher und Kochutensilien (Töpfe, Pfanne, Teller, Besteck etc.) zur Verfügung. 

Mit der Standheizung friert man auch an kalten Sommertagen nicht ;)

Bringe dennoch gerne einen eigenen Schlafsack mit und vllt auch ein Kissen und Kopflampe - evtl auch einen Kocher - kann "schlimmstenfalls" auch schauen ob ich das was Dir fehlt auch organisieren oder zur Verfügung stellen kann. 

Bei Fragen kannst du mich auch  gerne unter meiner Telefonnummer erreichen: 
+ (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) 
Ich wünsche Dir ein tolles Abenteuer!

name: Hotel in Zürich · ★New · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview: Nestled in the heart of the city, our hotel is a stone's throw from Zurich's vibrant nightlife, ensuring you're close to all the main party places. A mere 5-minute stroll from the hotel unveils a delightful Hammam, perfect for relaxation. The hotel's vicinity boasts a plethora of charming restaurants, mini-markets, and shops. Within a leisurely 10-minute walk, you'll reach Zurich's main train station, while tram and bus stops are conveniently located just 2 minutes away. Explore the city further – the main shopping street is a delightful 15-minute walk or a swift 5-minute journey by public transport.

name: Rental unit in Zürich · ★New · 2 bedrooms · 1 bed · 1 bath
Rental unit in Zürich · ★New · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in Zurich's Oerlikon district, a neighborhood seamlessly blending local culture, modern convenience, and a vibrant atmosphere. Here's a snapshot of what the area has to offer:

Diverse Cultural Fusion: Oerlikon's community is a melting pot of local and international residents, creating a vibrant cultural blend. While lacking the historical charm of Zurich's Old Town, Oerlikon delivers a contemporary Swiss urban experience, combining Swiss efficiency with cosmopolitan living.

Shopping Variety: The neighborhood features a diverse range of shops, from supermarkets to boutiques and specialty stores, catering to everyday needs and offering unique Swiss products.

Dining Delights: Oerlikon boasts an array of bars and restaurants serving Swiss and international cuisine, along with trendy dining options. Whether you crave Swiss classics like fondue or want to embark on a global culinary journey, Oerlikon has something for every palate.
host_about:
We turn temporarily vacant properties into contemporary furnished short-term rental apartments. 

Our apartments shall be functional and clean at a fair rate and our team can be reached 24/7 in order to assist you with anything you might need. 

Stay in our apartments without being guilty of contributing to gentrification. Our apartments are not being rented from the regular market to be let as furnished apartments. Properties we use are temporary empty and instead of staying empty are being furnished & rented to you for a limited amount of time.

neighborhood_overview:
Du wohnst im kontrastreichen und wunderschönen Quartier Höngg, direkt am Ufer der Limmat mit einzigartigem Ausblick. Nur ein paar Minuten zu Fuss entfernt liegt der Geheimtipp eines jeden Zürchers: Die Werdinsel, welche zu ausgedehnten Spaziergängen und im Sommer zum Badeplausch einlädt. Entlang der Limmat verläuft ein Fussweg, welcher für eine morgendliche Jogging-Runde oder einfach zu einem schönen Spaziergang einlädt.

Direkt neben der Unterkunft liegt die Bushaltestelle "Winzerhalde". Du gelangst also mit dem Bus bequem in die benachbarten Quartiere oder ins Zentrum von Zürich. Die weltberühmte Hochschule ETH Hönggerberg liegt ebenfalls nur eine Viertelstunde entfernt.
host_about:
Hey ich bin Patrick und wohne mit meiner Frau und meinen zwei Jungs in einem Vorort von Zürich. Meine Frau sagt immer, dass ich ein Social Butterfly sei, was ich bestätigen kann.
Ich freue mich jedenfalls, wenn ich dir als Gast in meiner Unterkunft ein tolles Erlebnis und schöne Erinnerungen bieten darf. Da wir selbst gerne umherreisen, weiss ich genau, wie wichtig das ist.
